<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910312-0052</DOCNO><DOCID>910312-0052.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- GAF Corp.:   Company's Losses Narrowed   In Fourth Quarter and Year</HL><DATE>03/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9</SO><CO>   GAF</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)</IN><LP>   GAF Corp. reported narrower losses for its fourth quarterand 1990 as it posted better operating results. In addition,the company recorded investment losses in the year-agoquarter.   GAF, a closely held Wayne, N.J., maker of specialtychemicals and building materials, had a quarterly net loss of$3.8 million compared with a loss of $20.2 million a yearearlier. Sales for the period declined slightly to $211.1million from $213 million. Operating earnings were up to$40.1 million from $36.5 million a year ago.</LP><TEXT>   GAF's losses are largely attributable to interest expenseson its debt, which it incurred in a management-led leveragedbuy-out in 1989. Interest expenses totaled $43.3 millioncompared with $44.5 million a year earlier.   Full-year losses totaled $10.4 million compared with 1989losses of $21.4 million. Sales rose to $921.6 million from$851.4 million.</TEXT></DOC>